### Phase 1: Backend — Add Sync Support

#### [MODIFY] [index.ts](file:///c:/Users/raksh/Desktop/GrocerySho_List/db/index.ts)

Add sync-enabling columns to every table:

```sql
-- Every table gets these new columns:
uuid VARCHAR(36) UNIQUE    -- Globally unique ID (for cross-device identity)
updated_at DATETIME        -- When was this last changed?
is_deleted BOOLEAN DEFAULT 0  -- Soft delete flag
```

**Why UUIDs?** Right now your tables use auto-increment IDs (`id INT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT`). The problem: if the mobile creates an item offline, it gets local ID `42`. Meanwhile the server also assigns ID `42` to a different item. UUIDs solve this — they're globally unique regardless of where they're generated.

**Why soft deletes?** If you truly `DELETE` a row from the server, the mobile will never know it was deleted. With `is_deleted`, the sync pull can say "this item was deleted, remove it locally too."

Changes:
- Add `uuid`, `updated_at`, `is_deleted` columns to all 6 tables
- Add migration logic to add columns to existing tables
- Add a trigger/default to auto-set `updated_at` on every INSERT/UPDATE

