## How the Complete Flow Works

### Scenario: User adds item on web while phone is offline

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Web as 🖥️ Web App
    participant Server as ☁️ Express + MySQL
    participant Phone as 📱 Mobile (Offline)
    
    Note over Phone: 📵 Phone is offline
    
    Web->>Server: POST /api/master-items {name: "Avocado"}
    Server->>Server: INSERT with uuid, updated_at = NOW()
    Server-->>Web: ✅ Item created
    
    Note over Phone: Some time passes...
    Note over Phone: 📶 Phone comes online!
    
    Phone->>Server: GET /api/sync/pull?since=<last_sync_time>
    Server-->>Phone: {masterItems: [{name: "Avocado", ...}]}
    Phone->>Phone: INSERT "Avocado" into local SQLite
    
    Note over Phone: User sees "Avocado" appear! ✨
```

### Scenario: User adds item on phone while offline

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Phone as 📱 Mobile (Offline)
    participant SQLite as 📦 Local SQLite
    participant Server as ☁️ Express + MySQL
    
    Note over Phone: 📵 Phone is offline
    
    Phone->>SQLite: INSERT "Mangoes" (uuid=abc, is_dirty=true)
    Note over Phone: UI shows "Mangoes" instantly!
    
    Note over Phone: 📶 Phone comes online!
    
    Phone->>Server: POST /api/sync/push [{uuid: "abc", table: "master_items", data: {name: "Mangoes"}}]
    Server->>Server: INSERT into MySQL
    Server-->>Phone: ✅ Synced
    Phone->>SQLite: UPDATE is_dirty = false WHERE uuid = "abc"
    
    Note over Phone: Now visible on web too! ✨
```

