## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **MySQL hosting**: Right now your MySQL runs on `localhost`. For the mobile app to connect over the internet (not just local Wi-Fi), you'll need to deploy the backend + MySQL somewhere. Are you planning to use a cloud provider (e.g., Railway, Render, AWS, or a VPS)? Or for now, are you only testing on the same Wi-Fi network?

> [!IMPORTANT]  
> **Scope of offline support**: Should **all** features work offline, or just viewing + adding items? For example, should "Complete Shopping List" (which records purchase history) also work offline?

> [!NOTE]
> **Multi-device conflict scenario**: If two users edit the same item at the same time (one on web, one on mobile), "last write wins" means one edit will be overwritten. For a grocery app this is fine. Just confirming you're okay with this approach?

